obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (40669)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40669&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Slum Areas`
  line `(Improvement and Clearance) Act, 1956.`
  line `(2) It extends to all Union territories except the Union territories of the Andaman and Nicobar Islands`
  line `and the Laccadive, Minicoy and Amindivi Islands.`
  line `(3) It shall come into force in a Union territory on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, appoint; and different dates may be appointed for different Union`
  line territories.
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 8th February, 1957 in respect of the Union territory of Delhi, vide Notification No. S.R.O. 421, dated 4th February, 1957, see`
  line `Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line `1st April, 1958 in respect of the Union territory of Tripura, vide Notification No. S.R.O. 414, dated 31st March, 1958, see`
  line `Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line `Extended to Pondicherry Act 26 of 1968.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (40670)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40670&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,―`
  line `(a) “Administrator” means the Administrator of a Union territory;`
  line `(b) “building” includes any structure or erection or any part of a building as so defined but does`
  line `not include plant or machinery comprised in a building;`
  line `(c) “competent authority” means such officer or authority as the Administrator may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, appoint as the competent authority for the purposes of this Act;`
  line `(d) “erection” in relation to a building includes extension, alteration or re-erection;`
  line ^2
  line `(e) “land” includes benefits to arise out of land, and things attached to the earth or permanently`
  line `fastened to anything attached to the earth;`
  line `(f) “occupier” includes―`
  line `(a) any person who for the time being is paying or is liable to pay to the owner the rent or any`
  line `portion of the rent of the land or building in respect of which such rent is paid or is payable;`
  line `(b) an owner in occupation of, or otherwise using his land or building;`
  line `(c) a rent-free tenant of any land or building;`
  line `(d) a licensee in occupation of any land or building; and`
  line `(e) any person who is liable to pay to the owner damages for the use and occupation of any`
  line `land or building;`
  line `(g) “owner” includes any person who is receiving or is entitled to receive the rent of any building`
  line `or land whether on his own account or on behalf of himself and others or as agent or trustee, or who`
  line `would so receive the rent or be entitled to receive it if the building or land were let to a tenant;`
  line `(h) “prescribed” means prescribed by rules made under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(i) “slum clearance” means the clearance of any slum area by the demolition and removal of`
  line `buildings therefrom;`
  line ^3
  line `(j) “work of improvement” includes in relation to any building in a slum area the execution of`
  line `any one or more of the following works, namely:―`
  line `(i) necessary repairs;`
  line `(ii) structural alterations;`
  line `(iii) provision of light points, water taps and bathing places;`
  line `(iv) construction of drains, open or covered;`
  line `(v) provision of latrines, including conversion of dry latrines into water-borne latrines;`
  line `(vi) provision of additional or improved fixtures or fittings;`
  line `(vii) opening up or paving of courtyards;`
  line `(viii) removal of rubbish; and`
  line `(ix) any other work including the demolition of any building or any part thereof which in the`
  line `opinion of the competent authority is necessary for executing any of the works specified above.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `2. Subs. by Act 43 of 1964, s. 2, for clauses (e) and (f) (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 43 of 1964, s. 2 (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (40671)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Declaration of slum areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40671&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the competent authority upon report from any of its`
  line `officers or other information in its possession is satisfied as respects any area that the buildings in that`
  line area―
  line `(a) are in any respect unfit for human habitation; or`
  line `(b) are by reason of dilapidation, overcrowding, faulty arrangement and design of such buildings,`
  line `narrowness or faulty arrangement of streets, lack of ventilation, light or sanitation facilities, or any`
  line `combination of these factors, are detrimental to safety, health or morals,`
  line `it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare such area to be a slum area.`
  line `(2) In determining whether a building is unfit for human habitation for the purposes of this Act,`
  line `regard shall be had to its condition in respect of the following matters, that is to say―`
  line `(a) repair;`
  line `(b) stability;`
  line `(c) freedom from damp;`
  line `(d) natural light and air;`
  line `(e) water supply;`
  line `(f) drainage and sanitary conveniences;`
  line `(g) facilities for storage, preparation and cooking of food and for the disposal of waste water;`
  line `and the building shall be deemed to be unfit as aforesaid if and only if it is so far defective in one or more`
  line `of the said matters that it is not reasonably suitable for occupation in that condition.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (40672)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power of competent authority to require improvement of buildings unfit for human habitation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `4. Ins. by Act 43 of 1964, s. 3 (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40672&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the competent authority upon report from any of its officers or other information`
  line `in its possession is satisfied that any building in a slum area is in any respect unfit for human habitation, it may, unless in its opinion the building is not capable at a reasonable expense of being rendered so fit,`
  line `serve upon the owner of the building a notice requiring him within such time not being less than thirty`
  line `days as may be specified in the notice to execute the works of improvement specified therein and stating`
  line `that in the opinion of the authority those works will render the building fit for human habitation:`
  line ^4
  line `Provided that where the owner of the building is different from the owner of the land on which the`
  line `building stands and the works of improvement required to be executed relate to provision of water taps,`
  line `bathing places construction of drains, open or covered, as the case may be, provision of water-borne`
  line `latrines or removal of rubbish and such works are to be executed outside the building, the notice shall be`
  line `served upon the owner of the land.`
  line `(2) In addition to serving a notice under this section on the owner, the competent authority may serve`
  line `a copy of the notice on any other person having an interest in the building ^4`
  line `or the land on which the`
  line `building stands whether as lessee, mortgagee or otherwise.`
  line `(3) In determining, for the purposes of this Act, whether a building can be rendered fit for human`
  line `habitation at a reasonable expense, regard shall be had to the estimated cost of the works necessary to`
  line `render it so fit and the value which it is estimated that the building will have when the works are`
  line completed.
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (40673)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Inforcement of notice requiring execution of works of improvement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `5. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40673&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a notice under`
  line `section 4 requiring the owner of the building ^5`
  line `or of the land on which the building stands, as the case`
  line `may be, to execute works of improvement is not complied with, then, after the expiration of the time`
  line `specified in the notice the competent authority may itself do the works required to be done by the notice.`
  line `(2) All expenses incurred by the competent authority under this section, together with interest, at such`
  line `rate as the Central Government may by order fix, from the date when a demand for the expenses is made`
  line `until payment, may be recovered by the competent authority from the owner of the building ^5`
  line `or of the`
  line `land on which the building stands, as the case may be, as arrears of land revenue:`
  line `Provided that if the owner proves that he―`
  line `(a) is receiving the rent merely as agent or trustee for some other person; and`
  line `(b) has not in his hands on behalf of that other person sufficient money to satisfy the whole`
  line `demand of the authority, his liability shall be limited to the total amount of the money which he has in`
  line `his hands as aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (40713)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Expenses of maintenance of works of improvement etc., to be recoverable from the occupiers of buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40713&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Where works of improvement have been executed in relation to any building in a slum`
  line `area in pursuance of the provisions of sections 4 and 5, the expenses incurred by the competent authority`
  line `or, as the case may be, any local authority in connection with the maintenance of such works of`
  line `improvement or the enjoyment of amenities and conveniences rendered possible by such works shall be`
  line `recoverable from the occupier or occupiers of the building as arrears of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (40675)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 7
  title `Restriction on building, etc., in slum areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes `6. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40675&sectionno=6A&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^6 (1) The competent authority may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, direct that no person shall erect any building in a slum area except`
  line `with the previous permission in writing of the competent authority.`
  line `(2) Every notification issued under sub-section (1) shall cease to have effect on the expiration of two`
  line `years from the date thereof except as respects things done or omitted to be done before such cesser.`
  line `(3) Every person desiring to obtain the permission referred to in sub-section (1) shall make an`
  line `application in writing to the competent authority in such form and containing such information in respect`
  line `of the erection of the building to which the application relates as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of such application, the competent authority, after making such inquiry as it considers`
  line `necessary, shall, by order in writing,―`
  line `(a) either grant the permission subject to such terms and conditions, if any, as may be specified in`
  line `the order; or`
  line `(b) refuse to grant such permission:`
  line `Provided that before making an order refusing such permission, the applicant shall be given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity to show cause why the permission should not be refused.`
  line `(5) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall apply to―`
  line `(a) any works of improvement required to be executed by a notice under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 4 or in pursuance of an undertaking given under sub-section (2) of section 7; or`
  line `(b) the erection of any building in any area in respect of which a slum clearance order has been`
  line `made under section 10.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (40676)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power of competent authority to order demolition of buildings unfit for human habitation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40676&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Where a competent authority upon a report from any of its officers or other information in`
  line `its possession is satisfied that any building within a slum area is unfit for human habitation and is not`
  line `capable at a reasonable expense of being rendered so fit, it shall serve upon the owner of the building, and`
  line `upon any other person having an interest in the building, whether as lessee, mortgagee or otherwise, a`
  line `notice to show cause within such time as may be specified in the notice as to why an order of demolition`
  line `of the building should not be made.`
  line `(2) If any of the persons upon whom a notice has been served under sub-section (1), appears in`
  line `pursuance thereof before the competent authority and gives an undertaking to the authority that such`
  line `person shall within a period specified by the authority execute such works of improvement in relation to`
  line `the building as will in the opinion of the authority render the building fit for human habitation, or that it`
  line `shall not be used for human habitation until the authority on being satisfied that it has been rendered fit`
  line `for that purpose cancels the undertaking, the authority shall not make any order of demolition of the`
  line building.
  line `(3) If no such undertaking as is mentioned in sub-section (2) is given, or if in a case where any such`
  line `undertaking has been given any work of improvement to which the undertaking relates is not carried out`
  line `within the specified period or the building is at any time used in contravention of the terms of the`
  line `undertaking, the competent authority shall forthwith make an order of demolition of the building`
  line `requiring that the building shall be vacated within a period to be specified in the order not being less than`
  line `thirty days from the date of the order, and that it shall be demolished within six weeks after the expiration`
  line `of that period.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (40677)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Procedure to be followed where demolition order has been made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40677&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an order for`
  line `demolition of a building under section 7 has been made the owner of the building or any other person`
  line `having an interest therein shall demolish that building within the time specified in that behalf by the`
  line `order; and if the building is not demolished within that time the competent authority shall enter and`
  line `demolish the building and sell the materials thereof.`
  line `(2) Any expenses incurred by the competent authority under sub-section (1), if not satisfied out of the`
  line `proceeds of sale of materials of the building shall be recoverable from the owner of the building or any`
  line `other person having an interest therein as arrears of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (40678)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power to declare any slum area to be a clearance area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40678&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the competent authority`
  line `upon a report from any of its officers or other information in its possession is satisfied as respects any`
  line `slum area that the most satisfactory method of dealing with the conditions in the area is the demolition of`
  line `all the buildings in the area, the authority shall by an order notified in the Official Gazette declare the area to be a clearance area, that is to say, an area to be cleared of all buildings in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act:`
  line `Provided that any building in the area which is not unfit for human habitation or dangerous or`
  line `injurious to health may be excluded from the declaration if the authority considers it necessary.`
  line `(2) The competent authority shall forthwith transmit to the Administrator a copy of the declaration`
  line `under this section together with a statement of the number of persons who on a date specified in the`
  line `statement were occupying buildings comprised in the clearance area.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (40679)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Slum clearance order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `7. Subs. by Act 43 of 1964, s. 6, for sub-section (7) (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40679&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after the competent authority has declared any`
  line `slum area to be a clearance area, it shall make a slum clearance order in relation to that area ordering the`
  line `demolition of each of the buildings specified therein and requiring each such building to be vacated`
  line `within such time as may be specified in the order and submit the order to the Administrator for`
  line confirmation.
  line `(2) The Administrator may either confirm the order in to or subject to such variations as he considers`
  line `necessary or reject the order.`
  line `(3) If the Administrator confirms the order, the order shall become operative from the date of such`
  line confirmation.
  line `(4) When a slum clearance order has become operative, the owners of buildings to which the order`
  line `applies shall demolish the buildings before the expiration of six weeks from the date on which the`
  line `buildings are required by the order to be vacated or before the expiration of such longer period as in the`
  line `circumstances of the case the competent authority may deem reasonable.`
  line `(5) If the buildings are not demolished before the expiration of the period mentioned in sub-section`
  line `(4) the competent authority shall enter and demolish the buildings and sell the materials thereof.`
  line `(6) Any expenses incurred by the competent authority in demolishing any building shall, if not`
  line `satisfied out of the proceeds of sale of materials thereof, be recoverable by the competent authority as`
  line `arrears of land revenue.`
  line ^7
  line `(7) Subject to the provisions of this Act, where a slum clearance order has become operative, the`
  line `owner of the land to which the order applies may re-develop the land in accordance with plans approved`
  line `by the competent authority and subject to such restrictions and conditions (including a condition with`
  line `regard to the time within which the re-development shall be completed), if any, as that authority may`
  line `think fit to impose:`
  line `Provided that an owner who is aggrieved by a restriction or condition so imposed on the user of his`
  line `land or by a subsequent refusal of the competent authority to cancel or modify any such restriction or`
  line `condition may, within such time as may be prescribed, appeal to the Administrator and the Administrator`
  line `shall make such order in the matter as he thinks proper and his decision shall be final.`
  line `(8) No person shall commence or cause to be commenced any work in contravention of a plan`
  line `approved or a restriction or condition imposed under sub-section (7).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (40680)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power of competent authority to re-develop clearance area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `8. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for section 11 (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40680&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^8 (1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in sub-section (7) of section 10, the competent authority may at any time after the land has been`
  line `cleared of the buildings in accordance with a slum clearance order but before the work of re-development`
  line `of that land has been commenced by the owner, by order, determine to re-develop the land if that`
  line `authority is satisfied that it is necessary in the public interest to do so.`
  line `(2) Where land has been cleared of the buildings in accordance with a slum clearance order, the`
  line `competent authority, if it is satisfied that the land has been, or is being, re-developed by the owner thereof`
  line `in contravention of plans approved by the authority or any restrictions or conditions imposed under`
  line `sub-section (7) of section 10 or has not been re-developed within the time, if any, specified under such`
  line `conditions, may, by order, determine to re-develop the land:`
  line `Provided that before passing such order, the owner shall be given a reasonable opportunity to show`
  line `cause why the order should not be passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (40681)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power of Central Government to acquire land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40681&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where on any representation from the`
  line `competent authority it appears to the Central Government that, in order to enable the authority to execute`
  line `any work of improvement in relation to any building in a slum area or to re-develop any clearance area, it`
  line `is necessary that land within, adjoining or surrounded by any such area should be acquired, the Central`
  line `Government may acquire the land by publishing in the Official Gazette a notice to the effect that the`
  line `Central Government has decided to acquire the land in pursuance of this section:`
  line `Provided that, before publishing such notice, the Central Government may call upon the owner of, or`
  line `any other person who, in the opinion of the Central Government, may be interested in, such land to show`
  line `cause why it should not be acquired; and after considering the cause, if any, shown by the owner or any`
  line `other person interested in the land, the Central Government may pass such order as it deems fit.`
  line `(2) When a notice as aforesaid is published in the Official Gazette, the land shall, on and from the`
  line `date on which the notice is so published, vest absolutely in the Central Government free from all`
  line encumbrances.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (40682)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Land acquired by Central Government to be made available to the competent authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `9. Added by Act 43 of 1964, s. 8 (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40682&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Where any land in a slum area or clearance area has been acquired under this Act the Central`
  line `Government shall make the land available to the competent authority for the purpose of executing any`
  line `work of improvement or carrying out any order of demolition or for the purpose of re-development:`
  line ^9
  line `Provided that where on any representation from the competent authority, the Central Government is`
  line `satisfied that any such land or any portion thereof is unsuitable for the purposes mentioned in this section,`
  line `the Central Government may use the land or allow it to be used for such other public purpose or purposes`
  line `as it may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (40683)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Right to receive compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40683&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Every person having any interest in any land acquired under`
  line `this Act shall be entitled to receive from the Central Government compensation as provided hereafter in`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (40684)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Basis for determination of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `10. Subs. by Act 43 of 1964, s. 9, for “in such proportion as he considers reasonable” (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40684&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The amount payable as compensation in respect`
  line `of any land acquired under this Act shall be an amount equal to sixty times the net average monthly`
  line `income actually derived from such land during the period of five consecutive years immediately`
  line `preceding the date of publication of the notice referred to in section 12.`
  line `(2) The net average monthly income referred to in sub-section (1) shall be calculated in the manner`
  line `and in accordance with the principles set out in the Schedule.`
  line `(3) The competent authority shall, after holding an inquiry in the prescribed manner, determine in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2) the net average monthly income actually derived from`
  line `the land and publish a notice in the Official Gazette specifying the amount so determined and calling`
  line `upon the owner of the land and every person interested therein to intimate to it before a date specified in`
  line `the notice whether such owner or person agrees to the amount so determined and if he does not so agree,`
  line `what amount he claims to be the net average monthly income actually derived from the land.`
  line `(4) Any person who does not agree to the amount of the net average monthly income determined by`
  line `the competent authority under sub-section (3) and claims a sum in excess of that amount may prefer an`
  line `appeal to the Administrator within thirty days from the date specified in the notice referred to in that`
  line sub-section.
  line `(5) On appeal the Administrator shall, after hearing the appellant, determine the, net average monthly`
  line `income and his determination shall be final and shall not be questioned in any court of law.`
  line
  line `(6) Where there is any building on the land in respect of which the net average monthly income has`
  line `been determined, no separate compensation shall be paid in respect of such building:`
  line `Provided that where the owner of the land and the owner of the building on such land are different,`
  line `the competent authority shall apportion the amount of compensation between the owner of the land and`
  line `the owner of the building ^10`
  line `in the same proportion as the market price of the land bears to the market price`
  line `of the building on the date of the acquisition.`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (40685)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Apportionment of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40685&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where several persons claim to be interested in the`
  line `amount of compensation determined under section 15, the competent authority shall determine the`
  line `persons who in its opinion are entitled to receive compensation and the amount payable to each of them.`
  line `(2) If any dispute arises as to the apportionment of compensation or any part thereof, or as to the`
  line `persons to whom the same or any part thereof is payable, the competent authority may refer the dispute to`
  line `the decision of the Administrator; and the Administrator in deciding any such dispute shall follow, as far`
  line `as may be, the provisions of Part III of the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894).`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (40686)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Payment of compensation or deposit of the same in court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40686&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the amount of`
  line `compensation has been determined, the competent authority shall on behalf of the Central Government`
  line `tender payment of, and pay, the compensation to the persons entitled thereto.`
  line `(2) If the persons entitled to compensation do not consent to receive it, or if there be any dispute as to`
  line `the title to receive compensation or as to the apportionment of it, the competent authority shall deposit the`
  line `amount of the compensation in the court of the District Judge and that court shall deal with the amount so`
  line `deposited in the manner laid down in sections 32 and 33 of the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894).`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (40687)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Powers of competent authority in relation to determination of compensation, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40687&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `competent authority may, for the purposes of determining the amount of compensation or apportionment`
  line `thereof, require, by order, any person to furnish such information in his possession as may be specified in`
  line `the order.`
  line `(2) The competent authority shall, while holding inquiry under section 15, have all the powers of a`
  line `civil court while trying a suit under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the`
  line `following matters, namely:―`
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line `(c) reception of evidence on affidavits;`
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record from any court or office;`
  line `(e) issuing commissions for examination of witnesses.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (40688)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Proceedings for eviction of tenants not to be taken without permission of the competent authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `11. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for section 19 (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40688&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `^11 (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, no`
  line `person shall, except with the previous permission in writing of the competent authority,―`
  line `(a) institute, after the commencement of the Slum Areas (Improvement and Clearance)`
  line `Amendment Act, 1964, any suit or proceeding for obtaining any decree or order for the eviction of a`
  line `tenant from any building or land in a slum area; or`
  line
  line `(b) where any decree or order is obtained in any suit or proceeding instituted before such`
  line `commencement for the eviction of a tenant from any building or land in such area, execute such`
  line `decree or order.`
  line `(2) Every person desiring to obtain the permission referred to in sub-section (1) shall make an`
  line `application in writing to the competent authority in such form and containing such particulars as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line `(3) On receipt of such application, the competent authority, after giving an opportunity to the parties`
  line `of being heard and after making such summary inquiry into the circumstances of the case as it thinks fit,`
  line `shall by order in writing, either grant or refuse to grant such permission.`
  line `(4) In granting or refusing to grant the permission under sub-section (3), the competent authority shall`
  line `take into account the following factors, namely:―`
  line `(a) whether alternative accommodation within the means of the tenant would be available to him`
  line `if he were evicted;`
  line `(b) whether the eviction is in the interest of improvement and clearance of the slum areas;`
  line `(c) such other factors, if any, as may be prescribed.`
  line `(5) Where the competent authority refuses to grant the permission, it shall record a brief statement of`
  line `the reasons for such refusal and furnish a copy thereof to the applicant.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (40689)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `12. Subs. by Act 43 of 1964, s. 11, for section 20 (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40689&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `^12 Any person aggrieved by an order of the competent authority refusing to grant the`
  line `permission referred to in sub-section (1) of section 6A or referred to in sub-section (1) of section 19 may,`
  line `within such time as may be prescribed, prefer an appeal to the Administrator and the Administrator may,`
  line `after hearing the appellant, decide such appeal and his decision shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_a:
  sectionId (40690)
  sectionNo 20A
  orderNo 22
  title `Restoration of possession of premises vacated by a tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content
  footnotes `13. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40690&sectionno=20A&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content:
  string
  line `^13 (1) Where a tenant in`
  line `occupation of any building in a slum area vacates any building or is evicted therefrom on the ground that`
  line `it was required for the purpose of executing any work of improvement or for the purpose of re-election of`
  line `the building, the tenant may, within such time as may be prescribed, file a declaration with the competent`
  line `authority that he desires to be replaced in occupation of the building after the completion of the work of`
  line `improvement or re-erection of the building, as the case may be.`
  line `(2) On receipt of such declaration, the competent authority, shall by order require the owner of the`
  line `building to furnish to it, within such time as may be prescribed, the plans of the work of improvement or`
  line `re-erection of the building and estimates of the cost thereof and such other particulars as may be`
  line `necessary and shall, on the basis of such plans and estimates and particulars, if any, furnished and having`
  line `regard to the provisions of sub-section (3) of section 20B and after holding such inquiry as it may think`
  line `fit, provisionally determine the rent that would be payable by the tenant if he were to be replaced in`
  line `occupation of the building in pursuance of the declaration made by him under sub-section (1).`
  line `(3) The rent provisionally determined under sub-section (2) shall be communicated in the prescribed`
  line `manner to the tenant and the owner.`
  line `(4) If the tenant after the receipt of such communication intimates in writing to the competent`
  line `authority within such time as may be prescribed that when he is replaced in occupation of the building in`
  line `pursuance of the declaration made by him under sub-section (1), he would pay to the owner until the rent`
  line `is finally determined under section 20B the rent provisionally determined under sub-section (2), the`
  line `competent authority shall direct the owner to place the tenant in occupation of the building after the`
  line `completion of the work of improvement or re-erection of the building, as the case may be, and the owner`
  line `shall be bound to comply with such direction.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_b:
  sectionId (40691)
  sectionNo 20B
  orderNo 23
  title `Rent of buildings in slum areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40691&sectionno=20B&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_20_b_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any building in a slum area is let to a tenant after`
  line `the execution of any work of improvement or after it has been re-erected, the rent of the building shall be`
  line `determined in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line `(2) Where any such building is let to a tenant other than a tenant who is placed in possession of the`
  line `building in pursuance of a direction issued under sub-section (4) of section 20A, the tenant shall be liable`
  line `to pay to the owner―`
  line `(a) if there is a general law relating to the control of rents in force in the area in which the`
  line `building is situated and applicable to that building, the rent determined in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of that law;`
  line `(b) if there is no such law in force in such area, such rent as may be agreed upon between the`
  line `owner and the tenant.`
  line `(3) Where any such building is let to a tenant in pursuance of a direction issued under sub-section (4)`
  line `of section 20A, the tenant shall, notwithstanding any law relating to the control of rents in force in the`
  line `area be liable to pay to the owner―`
  line `(a) if any work of improvement has been executed in relation to the building, an annual rent of a`
  line `sum equivalent to the aggregate of the following amounts, namely:―`
  line `(i) the annual rent the tenant was paying immediately before he vacated the building for the`
  line `purpose of execution of the work of improvement;`
  line `(ii) six per cent. of the cost of the work of improvement; and`
  line `(iii) six per cent. of a sum equivalent to the compensation payable in respect of any land`
  line `which may have been acquired for the purpose of effecting such improvement as if such land`
  line `were acquired under section 12 on the date of the commencement of the work of improvement;`
  line `(b) if the building has been re-erected, an annual rent of a sum equivalent to four per cent. of the`
  line `aggregate cost of reconstruction of the building and the cost of the land on which the building is`
  line re-erected.
  line `Explanation.―For the purposes of this clause, the cost of the land shall be deemed to be a sum`
  line `equivalent to the compensation payable in respect of the land if it were acquired under section 12 on`
  line `the date of commencement of the reconstruction of the building.`
  line `(4) The rent payable by a tenant in respect of any building under sub-section (3) shall, on an`
  line `application made by the tenant or the owner, be determined by the authority referred to in sub-section (5):`
  line `Provided that an application for determination of such rent by the owner or the tenant shall not,`
  line `except for sufficient cause, be entertained by such authority after the expiry of ninety days from the`
  line `completion of the work of improvement or re-erection of the building, as the case may be.`
  line `(5) The authority to which the application referred to in sub-section (4) shall be made, shall be―`
  line `(a) where there is a general law relating to the control of rents in force in the area in which the`
  line `building is situate, the authority to whom applications may be made for fixing of rents of buildings`
  line `situate in that area; and for the purpose of determining the rent under this section that authority may`
  line `exercise all or any of the powers it has under the said general law; and the provisions of such law`
  line `including provisions relating to appeals shall apply accordingly;`
  line `(b) if there is no such law in force in that area, such authority as may be specified by rules made`
  line `in this behalf by the Central Government and such rules may provide the procedure that will be`
  line `followed by that authority in determining the rent and also for appeals against the decision of such`
  line authority.
  line `(6) Where the rent is finally determined under this section, then the amount of rent paid by the tenant`
  line `shall be adjusted against the rent so finally determined and if the amount so paid falls short of, or is in`
  line `excess of, the rent finally determined, the tenant shall pay the deficiency, or be entitled to a refund, as the`
  line `case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (40692)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 24
  title `Chapter not to apply to eviction of tenants from certain buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40692&sectionno=21&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Chapter`
  line `shall apply to or in relation to the ^14`
  line `eviction under any law of a tenant from any building in a slum area`
  line `belonging to the Government, ^15`
  line `the Delhi Development Authority or any local authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `14. Subs. by Act 43 of 1964, s. 13, for “execution of any decree or order under any law for the eviction” (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  line `15. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for “the Delhi Improvement Trust” (w.e.f. 27-2-1965)`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (40693)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 25
  title `Powers of entry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40693&sectionno=22&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for any person authorised by the competent authority in this`
  line `behalf to enter into or upon any building or land in a slum area with or without assistants or workmen in`
  line `order to make any inquiry, inspection, measurement, valuation or survey, or to execute any work which is`
  line `authorised by or under this Act or which it is necessary to execute for any of the purposes or in pursuance`
  line `of any of the provisions of this Act or of any rule or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (40694)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 26
  title `Powers of inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40694&sectionno=23&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The competent authority may, by general or special order, authorise`
  line `any person―`
  line `(a) to inspect any drain, latrine, urinal, cesspool, pipe, sewer or channel in or on any building or`
  line `land in a slum area, and in his discretion to cause the ground to be opened for the purpose of`
  line `preventing or removing any nuisance arising from the drain, latrine, urinal, cesspool, pipe, sewer or`
  line `channel, as the case may be;`
  line `(b) to examine works under construction in the slum area, to take levels or to remove, test,`
  line `examine, replace or read any meter.`
  line `(2) If, on such inspection, the opening of the ground is found to be necessary for the prevention or`
  line `removal of a nuisance, the expenses thereby incurred shall be paid by the owner or occupier of the land or`
  line `building, but if it is found that no nuisance exists or but for such opening would have arisen, the ground`
  line `or portion of any building, drain, or other work opened, injured or removed for the purpose of such`
  line `inspection shall be filled in, reinstated, or made good, as the case may be, by the competent authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (40695)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power to enter land adjoining land where work is in progress.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40695&sectionno=24&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person authorised by`
  line `the competent authority in this behalf may, with or without assistants or workmen, enter on any land`
  line `within fifty yards of any work authorised by or under this Act for the purpose of depositing thereon any`
  line `soil, gravel, stone or other materials, or for obtaining access to such work or for any other purposes`
  line `connected with the carrying on of the same.`
  line `(2) The person so authorised shall, before entering on any land under sub-section (1), state the`
  line `purpose thereof, and shall, if so required by the occupier, or owner, fence off so much of the land as may`
  line `be required for such purpose.`
  line `(3) The person so authorised shall, in exercising any power conferred by this section, do as little`
  line `damage, as may be, and compensation shall be payable by the competent authority to the owner or`
  line `occupier of such land or to both for any such damage whether permanent or temporary`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (40696)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 28
  title `Breaking into buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40696&sectionno=25&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for any person authorised by the competent`
  line `authority in this behalf to make any entry into any place, to open or cause to be opened any door, gate or`
  line `other barrier―`
  line `(a) if he considers the opening thereof necessary for the purpose of such entry; and`
  line `(b) if the owner or occupier is absent, or being present refuses to open such door, gate or barrier.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (40697)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 29
  title `Entry to be made in the day time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40697&sectionno=26&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `No entry authorised by or under this Act shall be made`
  line `except between the hours of sunrise and sunset.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (40698)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 30
  title `Owner's consent ordinarily to be obtained.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes `16. Subs. by Act 43 of 1964, s. 14, for “No building or land” (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40698&sectionno=27&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line ^16
  line `Save as provided in this Act, no building or`
  line `land shall be entered without the consent of the occupier, or if there is no occupier, of the owner thereof, and no such entry shall be made without giving the said occupier or owner, as the case may be, not less`
  line `than twenty four hours’ written notice of the intention to make such entry:`
  line `Provided that no such notice shall be necessary if the place to be inspected is a shed for cattle or a`
  line `latrine, urinal or a work under construction.`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (40699)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power of eviction to be exercised only by the competent authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `17. Ins. by Act 43 of 1964, s. 15 (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40699&sectionno=28&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Where the competent`
  line `authority is satisfied either upon a representation from the owner of a building or upon other information`
  line `in its possession that the occupants of the building have not vacated it in pursuance of any notice, order or`
  line `direction issued or given by the authority, the authority shall, by order, direct the eviction of the occupants`
  line `from the building in such manner and within such time as may be specified in the order ^17`
  line `and for the`
  line `purpose of such eviction may use or cause to be used such force as may be necessary:`
  line `Provided that before making any order under this section the competent authority shall give a`
  line `reasonable opportunity to the occupants of the building to show cause why they should not be evicted`
  line therefrom.
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (40700)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to remove offensive or dangerous trades from slum areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40700&sectionno=29&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The competent authority`
  line `may, by order in writing, direct any person carrying on any dangerous or offensive trade in a slum area to`
  line `remove the trade from that area within such time as may be specified in the order:`
  line `Provided that no order under this section shall be made unless the person carrying on the trade has`
  line `been afforded a reasonable opportunity of showing cause as to why the order should not be made.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (40701)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 33
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40701&sectionno=30&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, any person aggrieved by any`
  line `notice, order or direction issued or given by the competent authority may appeal to the Administrator`
  line `within a period of thirty days from the date of issue of such notice, order or direction.`
  line `(2) Every appeal under this Act shall be made by petition in writing accompanied by a copy of the`
  line `notice, order or direction appealed against.`
  line `(3) On the admission of an appeal, all proceedings to enforce the notice, order or direction and all`
  line `prosecutions for any contravention thereof shall be held in abeyance pending the decision of the appeal,`
  line `and if the notice, order or direction is set aside on appeal, disobedience thereto shall not be deemed to be`
  line `an offence.`
  line `(4) No appeal shall be decided under this section unless the appellant has been heard or has had a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard in person or through legal practitioner.`
  line `(5) The decision of the Administrator on appeal shall be final and shall not be questioned in any court.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (40702)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 34
  title `Service of notices, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40702&sectionno=31&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every notice, order or direction issued under this Act shall, save as`
  line `otherwise expressly provided in this Act, be served―`
  line `(a) by giving or tendering the notice, order or direction, or by sending it by post to the person for`
  line `whom it is intended; or`
  line `(b) if such person cannot be found, by affixing the notice, order or direction on some conspicuous`
  line `part of his last known place of abode or business, or by giving or tendering the notice, order or`
  line `direction to some adult male member or servant of his family or by causing it to be affixed on some`
  line `conspicuous part of the building or land, if any, to which it relates.`
  line `(2) Where the person on whom a notice, order or direction is to be served is a minor, service upon his`
  line `guardian or upon any adult male member or servant of his family shall be deemed to be the service upon`
  line `the minor.`
  line `(3) Every notice, order or direction which by or under this Act is to be served as a public notice, order`
  line `or direction or as a notice, order or direction which is not required to be served to any individual therein`
  line `specified shall, save as otherwise expressly provided, be deemed to be sufficiently served if a copy`
  line `thereof is affixed in such conspicuous part of the office of the competent authority or in such other public place during such period, or is published in such local newspaper or in such other manner, as the`
  line `competent authority may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (40703)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 35
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `18. Subs. by Act 43 of 1964, s. 16 for “does any act in contravention of” (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40703&sectionno=32&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever ^18`
  line `fails to comply with any notice, order or direction issued or given`
  line `under this Act shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line `(2) Whoever commences or causes to be commenced any work in contravention of any restriction or`
  line `condition imposed under sub-section (7) of section 10 or any plan for the re-development of a clearance`
  line `area shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to three months, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line `(3) Whoever obstructs the entry of any person authorised under this Act to enter into or upon any`
  line `building or land or molests such person after such entry shall be punishable with fine which may extend`
  line `to one thousand rupees.`
  line `(4) If the person committing an offence under this Act is a company, every person who at the time the`
  line `offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible to, the company for the conduct of the`
  line `business of the company as well as the company, shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be`
  line `liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3) where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director or manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line `Explanation.―For the purposes of this section―`
  line `(a) “company” means a body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line `(b) “director” in relation to a firm means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (40704)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 36
  title `Order of demolition of buildings in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40704&sectionno=33&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line ^19
  line `(1) Where the erection of any building`
  line `has been commenced, or is being carried out, or has been completed, in contravention of any restriction or`
  line `condition imposed under sub-section (7) of section 10 or a plan for the re-development of any clearance`
  line `area or in contravention of any notice, order or direction issued or given under this Act the competent`
  line `authority may, in addition to any other remedy that may be resorted to under this Act or under any other`
  line `law, make an order directing that such erection shall be demolished by the owner thereof within such time`
  line `not exceeding two months as may be specified in the order, and on the failure of the owner to comply`
  line `with the order, the competent authority may itself cause the erection to be demolished and the expenses of`
  line `such demolition shall be recoverable from the owner as arrears of land revenue:`
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made unless the owner has been given a reasonable opportunity`
  line `of being heard.`
  line ^20
  line `(2) For the purpose of causing any building to be demolished under sub-section (1), the competent`
  line `authority may use or cause to be used such force as may be necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line `19. Section 33 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  line `20. Ins. by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (40705)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 37
  title `Jurisdiction of courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40705&sectionno=34&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `No court inferior to that of a magistrate of the first class shall try an`
  line `offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (40706)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 38
  title `Previous sanction of the competent authority or officers authorised by it, for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40706&sectionno=35&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for any offence punishable under this Act shall be instituted except with the previous`
  line `sanction of the competent authority or an officer authorised by the competent authority in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (40707)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40707&sectionno=36&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line ^21
  line `(1) The competent authority may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct that any power exercisable by it under this Act may also be exercised, in such cases and subject to`
  line `such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification, by such officer or the local authority as`
  line `may be mentioned therein.`
  line ^22
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that any power`
  line `exercisable by the Administrator under sub-section (7) of section 10, section 15, section 20 and section 30`
  line `may, subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification, be exercised also by the`
  line `Chief Secretary or by such other officer as may be mentioned therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `21 Section 36 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 43 of 1964, s. 18 (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  line `22. Ins. by s. 18, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (40708)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 40
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40708&sectionno=37&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the competent authority or against any person for anything which is in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done under this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37_a:
  sectionId (40709)
  sectionNo 37A
  orderNo 41
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_a_content
  footnotes `23. Ins. by s. 19, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40709&sectionno=37A&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_37_a_content:
  string
  line `^23 Save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, no civil court shall`
  line `have jurisdiction in respect of any matter which the competent authority or any other person is`
  line `empowered by or under this Act, to determine and no injunction shall be granted by any court or other`
  line `authority in respect of any action taken or to be taken in pursuance of any power conferred by or under`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (40710)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 42
  title `Competent authority, etc., to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes `24. Subs. by Act 58 of 1960, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for “him” (w.e.f. 26-12-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40710&sectionno=38&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `The competent authority and any person`
  line `authorised by ^24`
  line `it under this Act shall be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21`
  line `of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (40711)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 43
  title `Act to over-ride other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40711&sectionno=39&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder shall have`
  line `effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (40712)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 44
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555&sectionId=40712&sectionno=40&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00019_195696_1517807324555
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:―`
  line `(a) the manner, of authentication of notices, orders and other instruments of the competent`
  line authority;
  line `(b) the preparation of plans for the re-development of any slum area, and matters to be included in`
  line `such plans;`
  line ^25
  line `(bb) the form in which an application under sub-section (3) of section 6A shall be made and the`
  line `information to be furnished and the fees to be levied in respect of such application;`
  line `(bbb) the manner in which inquiries may be held under sections 15 and 19;`
  line `(c) the form and manner in which applications for permission under sub-section (2) of section 19`
  line `shall be made and the fees to be levied in respect of such applications;`
  line `(d) the procedure to be followed ^25`
  line `and the factors to be taken into consideration by the competent`
  line `authority before granting or refusing to grant permission under section 19;`
  line
  line `(e) the time within which an appeal may be preferred under ^26`
  line `sub-section (7) of section 10 or`
  line `section 20;`
  line ^27
  line `(ee) the time within which a declaration may be filed under sub-section (1) or an intimation may`
  line `be sent under sub-section (4) of section 20A and the fees, if any, to be levied in respect of such`
  line declaration;
  line `(eee) the time within which plans, estimates and other particulars referred to in sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 20A may be furnished;`
  line `(eeee) the procedure to be followed by the competent authority for fixing the provisional rent`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 20A;`
  line `(eeeee) the manner in which the rent provisionally determined under section 20A shall be`
  line `communicated to the tenants and owners;`
  line `(eeeeee) the matters in respect of which provision may be made under sub-section (5) of section`
  line 20B;
  line `(f) the officers and local authorities to whom powers may be delegated under section 36; and`
  line `(g) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line ^28
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or ^29`
  line `in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session, or the successive sessions aforesaid both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so however that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line `25. Ins. by Act 43 of 1964, s. 20 (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  line `26. Subs. by Act 43 of 1964, s. 20, for “section 20” (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  line `27. Ins. by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  line `28. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 27-2-1965).`
  line `29. Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 52, for “in two successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session in which it is so laid or`
  line `the session immediately following,” (w.e.f. 15-2-1986).`
